FINALLY, Bloemfontein Celtic are back to winning ways.Phunya Sele Sele beat Tshakhuma Tsha Madzivhandila (TTM) 1-0 at Dr. Petrus Molemela Stadium on Saturday. Sera Motebang scored the only goal of the match to hand John Maduka’s Siwelele all three points. Celtic broke an eight match winless run across all competitions which had seen them side slip to 13th spot, two points ahead of bottom-placed TTM. But the win saw them climb up to 12th spot with 13 points from 12 matches. Meanwhile, TTM have only registered one win this season and have failed to win their last nine league encounters. The Limpopo outfit has had a number of off the field struggles. They were recently sold to a corporation by the name of Protoscape 202 CC..The new owners will be hoping for better fortunes in the coming matches. TTM next face SuperSport United at Thohoyandou Stadium in the Nedbank Cup on Thursday. Celtic next face AmaZulu at Jonsson Kings Park Stadium on Tuesday. 